<form>
  <label>Basic table</label>

  <fieldset>
   <html>
    <div class="form_bg"><div class="content_width">
    <h1>Simple XML - Basic form search</h1>
    <p>
      This basic form search provides a text box to enter terms to search for, returning the results in a table.
    </p>
    <p>
      The search is specified using the following tags:
    </p>
    <div class="samplecode"><pre><![CDATA[
<searchTemplate> 
 index=_internal source=*metrics.log group=per_sourcetype_thruput series="$sourcetype$" 
 | head 1000 
</searchTemplate> 

<earliestTime>-30d</earliestTime> 
<latestTime>-0d</latestTime>]]></pre></div>
    
    <p>
      The default input type for &lt;fieldset&gt; is a text box. Within &lt;fieldset&gt; you also specify the search token:
    </p>
    <div class="samplecode"><pre><![CDATA[
<fieldset> 
   <input token="sourcetype" /> 
</fieldset>]]></pre></div>
    <p>
      Use &lt;html&gt; tags within the &lt;fieldset&gt; tag to display introductory text before the input field.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      For more information on basic forms, refer to the [Splunk documentation].
    </p>
    <h1>Source code</h1>
    <p>
      View the <a target="_blank" href="/static/app/dashboard_examples/samples/form_table_sample.html">source code to implement this form</a>. (Opens in a new window.)
    </p>
    
    <h1>What's next?</h1>
    <p>
      [<a href="/app/dashboard_examples/form_dropdown">Next: Form search with select dropdown</a>]
      <br />[<a href="/app/dashboard_examples/forms1">Prev: Forms using simple XML</a>]
    </p>
    <p>
      [<a href="../dashboard_examples/forms1">Simple XML Forms Home</a>]
      <br />[<a href="../dashboard_examples/dashboard0">Dashboard Examples Home</a>]
    </p>

    </div></div>
    <p style="padding-top: 6px"></p>
    <hr />
    <p style="padding-top: 20px">
      Enter a sourcetype in the field below to return the most recent 1000 events from the metrics log concerning that sourcetype.
    </p>
  </html>
   
     <!-- the default is a text box, with no seed value; if user does not input
          a value, then the $username$ token in searchTemplate will be removed -->
      <input token="sourcetype" />
  </fieldset>

  <!-- define master search template, with replacement tokens delimited with $ -->
  <searchTemplate>index=_internal source=*metrics.log group=per_sourcetype_thruput series="$sourcetype$" | head 1000</searchTemplate>
  <earliestTime>-30d</earliestTime>
  <latestTime>-0d</latestTime>
  
  <row>
      <!-- output the results as a 50 row events table -->
      <table>
        <title>Matching events</title>
        <option name="count">50</option>
      </table>
  </row>

</form>